Remarkable advances in NLP have been achieved with pre-trained language models (LMs) such as BERT [devlin2019bert] and GPT variants [radford2019language,GPT3].
LAMA [petroni2019language] designs methodology and datasets to probe masked LMs in order to acquire CSK that the models implicitly store.
COMET [bosselut2019comet] is a method that finetunes autoregressive LMs on CSK triples, and it can generate possible objects for a given pair of subject-predicate. However, the quality of the generated assertions is often considerably lower than that of the training data [nguyen-razniewski-2022-materialized]. 
